==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waler
<hw>Wal"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Wales</etsep>, i.e., New South Wales.]</ety> <def>A horse
imported from New South Wales; also, any Australian horse.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Kipling.</au></rj></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term originated in India, whither many horses are
exported from Australia (mostly from New South Wales), especially for
the use of cavalry.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Walhalla</ent>⟦br⟧
